


Installation and Setup Guide
Installation
Install MySQL by running the following command:
brew install mysql
Managing Service
Start the MySQL service:
brew services start mysql
Stop the MySQL service:
brew services stop mysql
Restart the MySQL service:
brew services restart mysql
Running
To run MySQL as the root user, use:
mysql -u root
If you do not need a background service and prefer running it manually, execute:
/opt/homebrew/opt/mysql/bin/mysqld_safe --datadir=/opt/homebrew/var/mysql
Security
By default, MySQL is installed without a root password. To improve security, execute:
mysql_secure_installation
To run MySQL with password, use:
mysql -u root -p
